# Figma Design System Rules — isabelthedesigner.com

## Component Organization

- UI components (Button, ProjectCard, etc.) go in `src/components/ui/`
- Layout components (Header, Footer, Section wrappers) go in `src/components/layout/`
- Spline 3D viewer components go in `src/components/spline/`
- Page components go in `src/pages/`
- Shared hooks go in `src/hooks/`
- IMPORTANT: Always check for an existing component before creating a new one

## Naming Conventions

- Component files: PascalCase (e.g., `ProjectCard.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (e.g., `useMediaQuery.ts`)
- All components export as default
- Component props use an interface named `{ComponentName}Props`

## Styling Rules

- IMPORTANT: Use Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes for all styling
- Design tokens are defined in `src/styles/index.css` inside the `@theme` block
- IMPORTANT: Never hardcode color hex values — use Tailwind token classes (e.g., `text-primary`, `bg-background`)
- IMPORTANT: Never hardcode spacing pixel values — use Tailwind spacing utilities
- Responsive breakpoints: `sm` (375px), `md` (768px), `lg` (1440px)
- Mobile-first approach: base styles are mobile, use `md:` and `lg:` for larger screens
- Animations use CSS transitions only — no extra animation libraries
- Custom interactive states (hover, pressed) for Button and ProjectCard will use CSS transitions/transforms

## Asset Handling

- Static images (PNG fallbacks for Spline, etc.) go in `public/images/`
- Self-hosted font files go in `public/fonts/`
- IMPORTANT: If the Figma MCP server returns a localhost source for an image or SVG, use that source directly
- IMPORTANT: DO NOT import or add new icon packages — all assets should come from the Figma payload
- IMPORTANT: DO NOT use or create placeholders if a localhost source is provided

## Figma MCP Integration — Required Flow

1. Run `get_design_context` first to fetch the structured representation for the exact node(s)
2. If the response is too large or truncated, run `get_metadata` to get the high-level node map, then re-fetch only the required node(s) with `get_design_context`
3. Run `get_screenshot` for a visual reference of the node variant being implemented
4. Only after you have both `get_design_context` and `get_screenshot`, download any assets needed and start implementation
5. Translate the output (usually React + Tailwind) into this project's conventions and tokens
6. Validate against Figma for 1:1 look and behavior before marking complete

## Implementation Rules

- Treat the Figma MCP output as a representation of design and behavior, not as final code style
- Map Figma colors, typography, and spacing to the Tailwind theme tokens in `src/styles/index.css`
- Reuse existing components from `src/components/` instead of duplicating functionality
- Use the `@/` path alias for all imports (e.g., `import Button from '@/components/ui/Button'`)
- Strive for 1:1 visual parity with the Figma design
- Validate the final UI against the Figma screenshot for both look and behavior

## Spline 3D Renders

- Use the `SplineViewer` component from `src/components/spline/SplineViewer.tsx`
- It renders `@splinetool/react-spline` on md+ screens and a fallback PNG on mobile
- The Spline runtime is lazy-loaded to avoid impacting initial bundle size

## Project-Specific Conventions

- TypeScript strict mode is enabled — all props must be typed
- React Router is used for routing — page components receive route props
- Path alias `@/*` maps to `src/*`
- Package manager: yarn (not npm)
